open-wifi-traffic-monitor - WiFi Traffic Monitor

USAGE:
    open-wifi-traffic-monitor <SSID>

DESCRIPTION:
    Capture HTTP traffic from open wireless networks. Connects to the
    specified SSID and monitors HTTP traffic (port 80) using tcpdump.

ARGUMENTS:
    SSID
        The SSID to connect and monitor traffic (required)

CONFIGURATION:
    -conf-open-wifi-traffic-monitor-interface INTERFACE
        Network interface to use for capture

    -conf-open-wifi-traffic-monitor-capture-file FILE
        File to write captured traffic to

NOTE:
    Requires root privileges. Press Ctrl+C to stop capture.

EXAMPLES:
    open-wifi-traffic-monitor "FreeWiFi"
    open-wifi-traffic-monitor "CoffeeShop"
